Cerca De Leticia, Colombia
June 22, 1952 Km 10240

2017
01:51:47,952 --> 01:51:52,582
Caracas, Venezuela
July 26, 1952 Km 12425

2018
01:51:54,876 --> 01:51:56,47.753846153616905
I'd prepared a speech 
<i>Había planeado un discurso</i>

2019
01:51:56,48.753846153616905 --> 01:51:58,408
full of anecdotes and grandiose phrases
<i>con anécdotas y frases grandiosas.</i>

2020
01:51:58,479 --> 01:52:00,674
I can't remember shit now
<i>No me acuerdo un carajo.</i>

2021
01:52:00,715 --> 01:52:02,682
That's how it goes
<i>Así pasa.</i>

2022
01:52:02,750 --> 01:52:05,412
Che What?
<i>Che. Ey.</i>

2023
01:52:07,388 --> 01:52:09,86.66666666697711
Still have time to come
<i>Todavía estás a tiempo de venirte</i>

2024
01:52:09,87.66666666697711 --> 01:52:11,347
work with me in Cabo Blanco
<i>a laburar conmigo a Cabo Blanco, ¿eh?</i>

2025
01:52:11,992 --> 01:52:13,860.0754716983065
If you want, graduate and return
<i>Si querés, recibite y venite. </i>

2026
01:52:13,861.0754716983065 --> 01:52:15,086
I'll wait for you
<i>Te espero.</i>

2027
01:52:15,162 --> 01:52:17,653
I don't know
<i>No sé.</i>

2028
01:52:18,799 --> 01:52:21,150
I just don't know
<i>No lo sé.</i>

2029
01:52:22,504 --> 01:52:24,515.3600000003353
Look, Mial, all this time 
<i>Mirá, mial. Todo este tiempo</i>

2030
01:52:24,516.3600000003353 --> 01:52:26,538
we spent on the road
<i>que pasamos en la ruta...</i>

2031
01:52:28,050 --> 01:52:30,838
something happened
<i>Sucedió algo.</i>

2032
01:52:32,789 --> 01:52:34,581.3773584906012
Something I'll have to think about
<i>Algo que tengo que pensar</i>

2033
01:52:34,582.3773584906012 --> 01:52:36,476
for a long time
<i>por mucho tiempo.</i>

2034
01:52:46,060 --> 01:52:48,402
So much injustice
<i>Cuánta injusticia, ¿no?</i>

2035
01:52:52,934 --> 01:52:55,153.20000000018626
Come on, the plane's taking off!
<i>- Vamos. Que sale el avión.</i>

2036
01:52:55,154.20000000018626 --> 01:52:56,500
Well, I should go
<i>- Che, me voy.</i>

2037
01:52:56,570 --> 01:52:57,295.7555555552244
Wait, wait.
<i>Pará, pará.</i>

2038
01:52:57,296.7555555552244 --> 01:52:59,539
take this, it may help
<i>Por ahí, esto te puede ayudar.</i>

2039
01:53:01,609 --> 01:53:02,946.6774193551391
- You kept it?
<i>- ¿Lo guardaste?</i>

2040
01:53:02,947.6774193551391 --> 01:53:04,571
- It's yours.
<i>- Es tuyo.</i>

2041
01:53:05,697 --> 01:53:08,078
- I'd better go. - Yes.
<i>- Che, me voy. - Sí.</i>

2042
01:53:18,501 --> 01:53:20,924
I'll write, okay?
<i>Te escribo, ¿eh?</i>

2043
01:53:29,970 --> 01:53:32,302
Fuser!
<i>Fuser.</i>

2044
01:53:37,770 --> 01:53:41,370
I have something very important to say
<i>No. Te quería decir algo muy importante.</i>

2045
01:53:41,448 --> 01:53:42,935.4482758622617
My birthday is not in April 2nd,
<i>Yo no cumplo años el 2 de abril.</i>

2046
01:53:42,936.4482758622617 --> 01:53:44,217
it's on August 8th
<i>Cumplo el 8 de agosto.</i>

2047
01:53:44,218 --> 01:53:45,752.6808510636911
- I just said that to motivate us.
<i>- Te lo dije para motivarte, nomás.</i>

2048
01:53:45,753.6808510636911 --> 01:53:46,345
- I know.
<i>- Ya sé.</i>

2049
01:53:46,404 --> 01:53:48,803.4512195121497
- You knew it? Son-of-a-bitch!
<i>- ¿Ya sabías? Hijo de puta.</i>

2050
01:53:48,804.4512195121497 --> 01:53:49,683.25
- Yeah.
<i>- Sí.</i>

2051
01:54:03,505 --> 01:54:04,659.1621621623635
- So long, Mial!
<i>- Hasta luego, mial.</i>

2052
01:54:04,660.1621621623635 --> 01:54:06,301
- Bye, my friend.
<i>- Chau, amigo.</i>

2053
01:54:40,808 --> 01:54:42,236.0526315793395
This isn't a tale 
<i>No es éste el relato</i>

2054
01:54:42,237.0526315793395 --> 01:54:44,744
of heroic feats.
<i>de hazañas impresionantes.</i>

2055
01:54:44,754 --> 01:54:47,35.77631578966975
It's about two lives in a moment 
<i>Es un trozo de dos vidas en un momento</i>

2056
01:54:47,36.77631578966975 --> 01:54:50,114
running together on the same path,
<i>en que cursaron juntas un mismo trecho</i>

2057
01:54:50,184 --> 01:54:51,765.5
with common aspirations 
<i>con identidad de aspiraciones</i>

2058
01:54:51,766.5 --> 01:54:53,471
and similar dreams.
<i>y conjunción de ensueños.</i>

2059
01:54:54,822 --> 01:54:56,640.5714285718277
Was our perspective
<i>¿Fue nuestra visión</i>

2060
01:54:56,641.5714285718277 --> 01:55:00,852
too narrow, too biased, too hasty?
<i>demasiado estrecha, parcial, apresurada?</i>

2061
01:55:00,928 --> 01:55:02,596.9215686274692
Were our conclusions 
<i>¿Fueron nuestras conclusiones</i>

2062
01:55:02,597.9215686274692 --> 01:55:03,863
too rigid?
<i>demasiado rígidas?</i>

2063
01:55:04,983 --> 01:55:06,933
Maybe.
<i>Tal vez.</i>

2064
01:55:07,935 --> 01:55:09,267.3846153849736
The aimless wandering 
<i>Pero ese vagar sin rumbo</i>

2065
01:55:09,268.3846153849736 --> 01:55:11,166
around our massive America
<i>por nuestra mayúscula América</i>

2066
01:55:11,238 --> 01:55:14,401
has changed me more than I thought.
<i>me ha cambiado más de lo que creí.</i>

2067
01:55:14,475 --> 01:55:17,828
I am not me anymore,
<i>Yo ya no soy yo.</i>

2068
01:55:17,829 --> 01:55:21,312
at least I'm not the same me I was.
<i>Por lo menos, no soy el mismo yo interior.</i>

2069
01:56:55,176 --> 01:57:00,264
It took eight years for Ernesto
and Alberto to meet again

2070
01:57:01,641 --> 01:57:05,603
In 1960 Granado was invited
to live and work in Cuba

2071
01:57:05,770 --> 01:57:07,689
The invitation
came from his old friend Fuser,

2072
01:57:07,855 --> 01:57:09,816
now "Comandante" Ernesto Che Guevara,

2073
01:57:09,982 --> 01:57:13,986
one of the most prominent and inspiring
leaders of the Cuban Revolution

2074
01:57:14,987 --> 01:57:19,200
Che went on to fight for his ideals in the
Congo and Bolivia where he was captured,

2075
01:57:19,367 --> 01:57:23,329
and with the support of the CIA,
murdered in October 1967

2076
01:57:24,330 --> 01:57:26,499
Forever faithful to his friend Fuser,

2077
01:57:26,666 --> 01:57:30,753
Granado remained in Cuba where he founded
the Santiago School of Medicine

2078
01:57:30,920 --> 01:57:35,007
He lives in Havana with his wife Delia,
their children and grandchildren

